description.narrative: Eswatini - Malaria - National Emergency Response Council on HIV and AIDS - NERCHA. This program has the following goals: Eliminate Malaria from Eswatini by 2023. The objectives of this program are: To achieve 100% coverage of at-risk populations with appropriate vector control interventions in residual non-active and active foci and areas with high malariogenic potential according to national guidelines by 2023.. To test 100% of suspected malaria cases with quality assured diagnostics and assure prompt and effective treatment to confirmed cases according to national guidelines.. To interrupt malaria transmission in all foci and epidemics through timely notification of cases, accurate identification of likely locations of transmission and application of effective interventions by 2023.. To empower all the population to adopt malaria prevention and control practices by 2023.. To expand and maintain multi-sectoral partnerships and capacity for effective programme management and coordination at all levels.. To reach 95% of high risk populations with an appropriate mix of interventions.
